See:

	http://www.vips.ecs.soton.ac.uk/index.php?title=Build_on_OS_X

Steps:

1) install gtk-osx
2) jhbuild bootstrap
3) jhbuild build meta-gtk-osx-bootstrap
4) jhbuild build meta-gtk-osx-core
5) append 
	moduleset = "file:///Users/john/package/vips/jhbuild/vips-osx.modules"
   to ~/.jhbuild-custom
6) jhbuild build nip2
7) jhbuild run nip2 to test the build
8) ./package-nip2.sh

will generate ~/Desktop/nip2-x.x.x.app, using the binary in ~/gtk/inst

Next, use Disc Utility to make a .dmg. Start Disk Utility, click File / New /
Disc Image from Folder, pick nip2-x.x.x.app

